Photo by @amivitale // Don't mind me, I'll help myself! In a noisy, slurpy affair, orphaned elephants at Reteti Elephant Sanctuary (@r.e.s.c.u.e) get a bottle of milk formula every three hours around the clock. Reteti is the first-ever community-owned elephant sanctuary in Africa.
The orphans arrive at the sanctuary as a result of human-elephant conflict, climate-related issues, and some rare cases of poaching, where they are nursed back to health by dedicated keepers and later, released back into the wild.

@r.e.s.c.u.e is celebrating its sixth anniversary. Follow @amivitale and @r.e.s.c.u.e to learn more, including how you can help.
